#how to assign permissions 
# Read (r): 4
# Write (w): 2
# Execute (x): 1

-> sudo chmod 777 /path/filename
#it will assign all the permissons rwx for user, group, and others
-> sudo chmod 666 /path/filename
#it will have read adn write permissons for user.group, and others

#if we wants to change all the permissons for all the files in a folder to unly read and write then
->sudo chmod -f 666 -R *
